If you build and publish the project by build server, and manage the version by Git, you can try Msbuild [GitVersion](https://gitversion.readthedocs.io/en/latest/usage/msbuild-task/) task. Similar issue see [here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/49765756/c-net-how-to-generate-and-increase-package-version-automatically-especially).

But if you just want a clean build and publish in local VS without using Git, then I&#39;m afraid for now there&#39;s no VS option or [Msbuild Task](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/visualstudio/msbuild/msbuild-task-reference?view=vs-2019) support this behavior. You can go [DC](https://developercommunity.visualstudio.com/spaces/8/index.html) to suggest the feature  cause it&#39;s a meaningful idea, but currently it&#39;s not available.

Also, hints from [Martin](https://stackoverflow.com/a/47819996/10910450) and [Alexandre](https://stackoverflow.com/a/57433541/10910450), you can add this script into xx.csproj:

      &lt;PropertyGroup&gt;
        &lt;GenerateNuspecDependsOn&gt;$(GenerateNuspecDependsOn);SetPackageVersion&lt;/GenerateNuspecDependsOn&gt;
      &lt;/PropertyGroup&gt;
    
      &lt;Target Name=&quot;SetPackageVersion&quot; DependsOnTargets=&quot;Build&quot;&gt;
        &lt;PropertyGroup&gt;
          &lt;!--&lt;PackageVersion&gt;$([System.DateTime]::Now.ToString(&amp;quot;yyyy.MM.dd.HHmmss&amp;quot;))&lt;/PackageVersion&gt;--&gt;
          &lt;!--You can customize the format and the rule about how version increases here.--&gt;
          &lt;PackageVersion&gt;$([System.DateTime]::Now.ToString(&amp;quot;1.MM.dd&amp;quot;))&lt;/PackageVersion&gt;
        &lt;/PropertyGroup&gt;
      &lt;/Target&gt;

Then when you publish the package today, its version is 1.10.4. Tomorrow for 1.10.5, it works if you don&#39;t really need to publish different versions of one package in a day. Also you can customize the script to define your version-increasing rule. May it helps:)

***

If targeting multiple frameworks, see https://stackoverflow.com/questions/48065516/build-project-with-multiple-targetframeworks-in-tfs-as-nuget-package

